# Environment Configuration

Never read `process.env.BASE_API_HOSTNAME` directly. Use the helpers from `@/lib/env`:

```ts
import { imageGenerationBase } from '@/lib/env';
import { platformApiBase } from '@/lib/env';

// Image-generation service endpoints
const url = `${imageGenerationBase()}/prompt-versions`;

// Platform APIs (studio, spatial, projects) — always https
const url = `${platformApiBase()}/studio/v1/design-packages`;
```

- `imageGenerationBase()` returns `"{BASE_API_HOSTNAME}/image-generation/v1"`
- `platformApiBase()` returns `"https://{BASE_API_HOSTNAME}"` (protocol-normalized)
- Both throw if the env var is missing — let callers catch or let it bubble
- These are **server-only** — never import in `'use client'` components
- Browser code should use `serviceUrl()` from `@/lib/api-base` which proxies through `/api/v1/image-generation/`
